Font Awesome a Laravel
---------------------------------------------------------------------
Blog:  https://medium.com/@ewave80/adding-font-awesome-to-laravel-5-8-4dbb4ac4adfa
Watch: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XPH2fatTLVg

1. $ cd (navigate) into your project directory.

2. $ npm install

3. In a browser go to https://fontawesome.com/
	3.1 click on the “ Start for free” button.scroll down 
	3.2 and click on icon npm
	https://fontawesome.com/how-to-use/on-the-web/setup/using-package-managers
	3.3 copy and past in your Laravel project directory and hit enter to install
	$ npm install --save @fortawesome/fontawesome-free

4. after a successful installation, you should check your package.json

5. $ npm run watch

6. let import font-awesome from node_module.
	../resources/sass/app.scss

	@import '~@fortawesome/fontawesome-free/scss/fontawesome.scss';

7. let head back to Font-Awesome Official website. click on the button Start for free and select the SASS (scss) button.
	7.1 Adding Font Awesome to Your Compile
	7.2 Open your project’s ../resources/sass/variables.scss 
		and edit the $fa-font-path variable to point 
		to where you placed the webfonts folder.
		7.2.1 Add $fa-font-path:        "../webfonts"; to file sass/variables.scss
		7.2.2 Add $fa-font-path:        "../webfonts"; to file sass/app.scss

8.  import solid.css from node_module. (../resources/sass/app.scss)
	@import '~@fortawesome/fontawesome-free/scss/solid.scss';
	@import '~@fortawesome/fontawesome-free/scss/brands.scss';

9. Try
